Installing docker for our project on ubuntu.
  >installing command : sudo-apt install docker.io

FROM--> installing operating system like ubuntu which already has python in it.
RUN--> running any command such as running a python command for downloading the django app.
COPY . . (FIRST DOT IS SOURCE, SECOND IS DESTINATION)



  BuILD  command -->  docker build . -t "msg"( will build all the docker files 


running a docker file:

                                              sudo docker build . - t messagewithoutapostophes::
Image is built and gives us an Image id.

To check the state of image :
>sudo docker ps 

                                              

to run the file   
sudo docker run -p   8001:8001 (image id )                                         
                                              
